name: ONLINE GIFT CARD -$50
description:

There are three options to purchase, $50, $75, $100. You can buy one or more to create the desired amount you wish to gift. If you buy more than one, please indicate if this is meant for the same recipient or different ones.

With your purchase, please provide the name of your recipient(s) so a personal online coupon code can be created for her.

An email will be sent to you within a day with a printable gift card and personalized code. You can request a hard copy to be mailed to you.

No amount of the gift card cannot be returned or exchanged for cash.

name: THE BALL OF THE CENTURY
description:
The Party Collection is inspired by epic ragers throughout history. The chosen parties range in time period, culture, intention, but they share the desire to let go and escape into an elevated intoxicated rapturous fantasy.

This necklace is inspired by the 1951 Beistegui Ball in Venice, often referred to as "The Ball of the Century." The party was a total lavish spectacle that drew from an 18th century theme.

Two strands of navy and gray painted wood, faux rhinestones, gray smoky quartz and chunky pyrite. 

Approximately 17" at its shortest strand.

name: BLACK AND WHITE BALL
description:
The Party Collection is inspired by epic ragers throughout history. The chosen parties range in time period, culture, intention, but they share the desire to let go and escape into an elevated intoxicated rapturous fantasy.

This statement necklace draws from Truman Capote's Black and White Masquerade Ball of 1966 at the Plaza Hotel in Manhattan. In honor of publisher Katharine Graham, the party was based off My Fair Lady's Ascot race scene and was a celebration of Capote's personal achievements in wealth, status and literature.

Two strands of black swarovski crystal, painted wood, faux enamel rhinestones, gray smoky quartz, gold plated brass tubes and faceted glass. 

Approximately 17" at its shortest strand.
